            "answer_text": "Unlike many of the other commenters, I'm not annoyed or offended by this question. It's a fair one as long as the asker is as genuine as he sounds.  I'm not going to be able to find this article, so I'm going to need to summarize it from memory. The president of the Florida Holocaust Museum, John Loftus, wrote on this topic and has a very good answer. Basically he says that while there have been many other genocides, the holocaust was the only genocide that was done specifically for the end goal of murdering all members of a specific group. All other genocides in history were land and resource grabs. The US killed off the Native Americans for land. The Turks murdered the Armenians for their land and property. Darfur was a grab for oil-rich land. Etc. He wasn't saying that there wasn't a race or ethnic cleansing reason for each of these, but the underlying motive was property. This is simply not so with the holocaust whose main goal was the extermination of all Jews. Other groups involved and property taken were all secondary motives, and there's plenty of evidence for this.  So, I think it is fair to say that it is not overstated. It's very scary, and I think many are legitimately afraid it will happen again if people are not properly educated on this subject. ",
