            "answer_text": "Not at all. There hasn't been a genocide that has been as systematic, humiliating and rapid as the Holocaust. And the worst part is no matter how much heroics you want to paint/brush the Allies with, what was going on with the Jewish community during World War II  was something that was very low on their list of priorities. And that is a very painful thing to accept that everybody should be ashamed of. And this needs to be said as many times as possible as this can NEVER happen again. And furthermore, although I am not Jewish, we should also remind ourselves what the Jewish community has been through not just in World War II but over the course  of history in human mankind.  Make sure your memory is long when you look back in history, not short. ",
